   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Trinity Hippocampal Learning Probe — Long-Context Retention\n",
    "\n",
    "**Task 5 of 25** | Track 1: Learning | Brain Zone: HIPPOCAMPUS\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook measures a model's ability to retain information across long contexts.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Trinity Neuroanatomical Foundation\n",
    "\n",
    "The **Hippocampus** in Trinity implements consolidation with φ-scaling:\n",
    "\n",
    "```zig\n",
    "// src/tri/brain/hippocampus_training.zig\n",
    "pub const ConsolidationConfig = struct {\n",
    "    capacity: usize,  // Fibonacci: 3, 5, 8, 13, 21\n",
    "    decay_rate: f32,\n",
    "    replay_frequency: u64,\n",
    "};\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Ternary Scoring {-1, 0, +1}\n",
    "\n",
    "- **+1 (correct)**: Model retrieves information correctly\n",
    "- **0 (partial)**: Model shows uncertainty but directionally correct\n",
    "- **-1 (wrong)**: Model fails to retain or hallucinates\n",
    "\n",
    "### φ-Scaling\n",
    "\n",
    "Context lengths follow Fibonacci: 3, 5, 8, 13, 21 items/facts"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install Kaggle Benchmarks SDK\n",
    "!pip install -q kaggle-benchmarks"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import kaggle_benchmarks as kbench\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from dataclasses import dataclass\n",
    "from typing import Literal\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load generated dataset\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('../../data/thlp_learning.csv')\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(df)} items\")\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Filter for long context retention task\n",
    "context_df = df[df['task'] == 'Long-Context Retention'].copy()\n",
    "print(f\"Long-context items: {len(context_df)}\")\n",
    "context_df[['id', 'task', 'question', 'answer', 'context_length', 'difficulty']].head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define structured output for context retention\n",
    "@dataclass\n",
    "class ContextRetentionResponse:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Model's response from long context.\"\"\"\n",
    "    answer: str  # Retrieved answer\n",
    "    confidence: float  # 0.0 to 1.0\n",
    "    retrieval_difficulty: float  # Self-reported difficulty (0-1)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def ternary_score(self, expected_answer: str) -> Literal[-1, 0, 1]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Return Trinity ternary score {-1, 0, +1}.\"\"\"\n",
    "        # Correct: exact match\n",
    "        if self.answer == expected_answer:\n",
    "            return 1\n",
    "        # Partial: contains correct info with uncertainty\n",
    "        elif self.retrieval_difficulty > 0.5 and self.confidence < 0.7:\n",
    "            return 0\n",
    "        # Wrong: incorrect or overconfident\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            return -1\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"ContextRetentionResponse schema defined\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define Kaggle benchmark task\n",
    "@kbench.task(name=\"trinity_hippocampus_context_retention\")\n",
    "def long_context_retention(\n",
    "    llm: kbench.LLM,\n",
    "    question: str,\n",
    "    expected_answer: str,\n",
    "    context_length: int\n",
    ") -> float:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Measure model's long-context retention ability.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        Retention score: 1.0 (perfect) to -1.0 (worst)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    prompt = f\"\"\"Read the following context carefully and answer the question.\n",
    "\n",
    "Context length: {context_length} items/facts\n",
    "Question: {question}\n",
    "\n",
    "Provide:\n",
    "1. Your answer\n",
    "2. Your confidence (0.0 to 1.0)\n",
    "3. How difficult was retrieval (0.0 = easy, 1.0 = very hard)\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    response = llm.prompt(\n",
    "        prompt,\n",
    "        schema=ContextRetentionResponse\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Calculate ternary score\n",
    "    ternary = response.ternary_score(expected_answer)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Combine: 50% accuracy, 30% confidence, 20% difficulty bonus\n",
    "    accuracy = 1.0 if response.answer == expected_answer else -1.0\n",
    "    confidence_score = (response.confidence - 0.5) * 2  # [-1, 1]\n",
    "    difficulty_bonus = (1.0 - response.retrieval_difficulty) * 0.2  # [0, 0.2]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    final_score = 0.5 * accuracy + 0.3 * confidence_score + difficulty_bonus\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return max(-1.0, min(1.0, final_score))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Task 'trinity_hippocampus_context_retention' registered\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Run evaluation on a sample\n",
    "sample_df = context_df.head(10)  # Test with 10 items first\n",
    "\n",
    "results = long_context_retention.evaluate(\n",
    "    llm=[kbench.llm],  # Default test LLM\n",
    "    evaluation_data=sample_df\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Evaluation Results (Sample):\")\n",
    "print(f\"Mean Score: {results['score'].mean():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Std Dev: {results['score'].std():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Min: {results['score'].min():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Max: {results['score'].max():.4f}\")\n",
    "results.head()"
   ]
  },
